<subSubSection id="A1D565563F01FF97FF26FB26FB45FF18" lastPageId="53" lastPageNumber="54" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" type="description">
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F01FF96FF26FB26FEA8FAAA" blockId="52.[151,1436,1148,2041]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
Morphology. D VI + I,14; A I,13–14; P 17–18. Medium-sized goby with moderately long body, and large head with short, slightly acute and oblique snout. Caudal peduncle deep, but lower than body depth. Dorsal fins of similar height, the first dorsal fin may be slightly taller, with more or less rounded margin and no elongate spines. Caudal fin rounded. Scales present on body and on predorsal area, usually visible on photographs, at least dorsally (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F01FF96FADCFA8AFEDCFAAA" author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Sanda, R." pageId="52" pageNumber="53" pagination="1104 - 1124" refId="ref58613" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Sanda, R. (2016) A new species of Gobius (Perciformes: Gobiidae) from the Mediterranean Sea and the redescription of Gobius bucchichi. Journal of Fish Biology, 88, 1104 - 1124. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jfb. 12883" type="journal article" year="2016">Kovačić &amp; Šanda 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F01FF96FF26FAD2FE9FF91A" blockId="52.[151,1436,1148,2041]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
Live coloration. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F01FF96FE65FAD3FE90FA73" bold="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Body pale gray, pale yellowish, or yellowish brown with pattern of brown dots forming longitudinal lines.</emphasis>
Dots are most marked along the lateral midline but always remain separated and generally form a continuous row with no marked spaces (
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F01FF96FD4EFA1AFCE3FA56" box="[687,771,1436,1463]" captionStart="FIGURE 34" captionStartId="34.[151,250,1062,1086]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1038]" captionTargetId="figure-19@34.[151,1436,181,1038]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 34. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Gobius bucchichi. Photo by R. Pillon, Rab Island, Croatia, Northern Adriatic Sea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601950" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601950/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F01FF96FCF6FA1BFE99FA3A" bold="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Eyes with a conspicuous horizontal dark brown stripe through the center,</emphasis>
narrowly continuing on postorbital part of head as series of small close-set spots, 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F01FF96FAEDFA47FD78FA1F" bold="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">an irregular longitudinal marking along the upper iris,</emphasis>
a variable number of additional markings in orbit’s upper half 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F01FF96FA95FA63FE2CF9C3" bold="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">but unmarked in ventral half</emphasis>
, except sometimes with a small dot in its anterior portion. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F01FF96FB9AF98EFE96F98B" bold="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Snout with dark dashes forming M-shaped line. Usually it has only 2 longitudinal rows of dots on the cheek with a large unmarked area in the middle</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F01FF96FE69F9D6FE0BF98A" box="[392,491,1616,1643]" captionStart="FIGURE 33" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-18@33.[151,1436,181,1895]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 33. The mouth unmarked at corner in A) G. bucchichi and B) H. ingressus. Dark dot on the corner of the mouth in C) G. auratus, D) G. incognitus, E) G. xanthocephalus and F) G. fallax. Area marked with hollow circle. Photos by R. Svensen (A), S. Engin (B), M. Kovačić (C, D, F), and P. Louisy (E). C and F photographed in a tank." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601673" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601673/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Fig. 33a</figureCitation>
). Rarely, a few dots are visible also in the middle cheek but usually limited to the anterior part of the cheek, very close together, well aligned and not parallel to the lower row. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F01FF96FB27F9F2FD84F952" bold="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Posterior angle of mouth without a well-defined dark dot</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F01FF96FD92F91EFD33F952" box="[627,723,1688,1715]" captionStart="FIGURE 33" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-18@33.[151,1436,181,1895]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 33. The mouth unmarked at corner in A) G. bucchichi and B) H. ingressus. Dark dot on the corner of the mouth in C) G. auratus, D) G. incognitus, E) G. xanthocephalus and F) G. fallax. Area marked with hollow circle. Photos by R. Svensen (A), S. Engin (B), M. Kovačić (C, D, F), and P. Louisy (E). C and F photographed in a tank." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601673" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601673/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Fig. 33a</figureCitation>
), so the lower row of dots, which runs along the ventral edge of the cheek, starts with 2 dashes never preceded by a marked dot on the corner of the mouth (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F01FF96FB6EF93AFA78F937" author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Sanda, R." box="[1167,1432,1724,1753]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" pagination="1104 - 1124" refId="ref58613" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Sanda, R. (2016) A new species of Gobius (Perciformes: Gobiidae) from the Mediterranean Sea and the redescription of Gobius bucchichi. Journal of Fish Biology, 88, 1104 - 1124. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jfb. 12883" type="journal article" year="2016">Kovačić &amp; Šanda 2016</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F01FF96FF76F966FE93F91A" author="Renoult, J. P. &amp; Pillon, R. &amp; Kovacic, M. &amp; Louisy, P." box="[151,371,1760,1787]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" refId="ref63723" refString="Renoult, J. P., Pillon, R., Kovacic, M. &amp; Louisy, P. (2022) Frontiers in Fishwatching Series - Gobies of North-eastern Atlantic and the Mediterranean: Gobius and Thorogobius. Les cahiers de la fondation Biotope. [in press]" type="book" year="2022">
Renoult 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F01FF96FF16F967FEC8F91B" box="[247,296,1760,1786]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">et al</emphasis>
. 2022
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F01FF96FF26F882FD23F8FE" blockId="52.[151,1436,1148,2041]" box="[199,707,1796,1823]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
Similar species. 
<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F01FF96FE9EF882FDACF8FF" authorityName="Kovacic &amp; Sanda" authorityYear="2016" box="[383,588,1796,1822]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Gobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="incognitus">
