</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F01FF96FF26F8AEFC49F86A" blockId="52.[151,1436,1148,2041]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
Habitat. Infralittoral species, known from 
<quantity id="2E379B383F01FF96FD55F8AFFD1FF8A2" box="[692,767,1833,1859]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" unit="m" value="4.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="1.0">1–8 m</quantity>
depth from all kinds of rocky substrata: gravel, cobbles, boulders and bedrock, but on sand only when it is mixed with a hard substratum, never on pure sand. The substratum was bare or covered with short thallus algae (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F01FF96FD73F8F6FC7DF86A" author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Sanda, R." box="[658,925,1904,1933]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" pagination="1104 - 1124" refId="ref58613" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Sanda, R. (2016) A new species of Gobius (Perciformes: Gobiidae) from the Mediterranean Sea and the redescription of Gobius bucchichi. Journal of Fish Biology, 88, 1104 - 1124. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jfb. 12883" type="journal article" year="2016">Kovačić &amp; Šanda 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F01FF97FF26F812FB45FF18" blockId="52.[151,1436,1148,2041]" lastBlockId="53.[151,1437,151,249]" lastPageId="53" lastPageNumber="54" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
Geographic distribution. Presently known from the eastern coast of the Adriatic Sea, it is common from the Gulf of Trieste (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F01FF96FEF3F83EFDCDF832" author="Tiralongo, F. &amp; Pillon, R." box="[274,557,1976,2003]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" pagination="215 - 220" refId="ref65266" refString="Tiralongo, F. &amp; Pillon, R. (2020) New distributional records of Gobius bucchichi from the Mediterranean Sea and in situ comparisons with Gobius incognitus. Annales, Series Historia Naturalis, 30 (2), 215 - 220." type="journal article" year="2020">Tiralongo &amp; Pillon 2020</bibRefCitation>
) to southern 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F01FF96FD22F83EFCF5F833" box="[707,789,1976,2002]" name="Croatia" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Croatia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F01FF96FCC4F83EFBD3F832" author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Sanda, R." box="[805,1075,1976,2005]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" pagination="1104 - 1124" refId="ref58613" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Sanda, R. (2016) A new species of Gobius (Perciformes: Gobiidae) from the Mediterranean Sea and the redescription of Gobius bucchichi. Journal of Fish Biology, 88, 1104 - 1124. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jfb. 12883" type="journal article" year="2016">Kovačić &amp; Šanda 2016</bibRefCitation>
); there is only one record in the Ionian Sea from Butrint, southern 
<collectingCountry id="91D8764D3F01FF96FDF9F85AFD91F817" box="[536,625,2012,2038]" name="Albania" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Albania</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F01FF96FD9EF85AFC6BF816" author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Sanda, R." box="[639,907,2012,2041]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" pagination="1104 - 1124" refId="ref58613" refString="Kovacic, M. &amp; Sanda, R. (2016) A new species of Gobius (Perciformes: Gobiidae) from the Mediterranean Sea and the redescription of Gobius bucchichi. Journal of Fish Biology, 88, 1104 - 1124. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jfb. 12883" type="journal article" year="2016">Kovačić &amp; Šanda 2016</bibRefCitation>
), and a record in the Aegean Sea from Kondyli beach, eastern Peloponnese (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F00FF97FE05FF11FCE9FF50" author="Tiralongo, F. &amp; Pillon, R." box="[484,777,151,177]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="215 - 220" refId="ref65266" refString="Tiralongo, F. &amp; Pillon, R. (2020) New distributional records of Gobius bucchichi from the Mediterranean Sea and in situ comparisons with Gobius incognitus. Annales, Series Historia Naturalis, 30 (2), 215 - 220." type="journal article" year="2020">Tiralongo &amp; Pillon 2020</bibRefCitation>
). Population from the Black Sea more similar in pattern of coloration to 
<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F00FF97FEB0FF3DFE02FF34" authorityName="Steindachner" authorityYear="1870" box="[337,482,187,213]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Gobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bucchichi">
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F00FF97FEB0FF3DFE85FF34" box="[337,357,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F00FF97FE94FF3DFE02FF34" box="[373,482,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">bucchichi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than to 
<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F00FF97FDA3FF3DFD3BFF35" authorityName="Kovacic &amp; Sanda" authorityYear="2016" box="[578,731,187,213]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Gobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="incognitus">
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F00FF97FDA3FF3DFDB6FF34" box="[578,598,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F00FF97FD87FF3DFD3BFF35" box="[614,731,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">incognitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in absence of black dot at the corner of mouth and any mark ventrally on iris (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F00FF97FEB6FF59FDE3FF18" author="Vasil'eva, E. D." box="[343,515,223,249]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" refId="ref65796" refString="Vasil'eva, E. D. (2007) Fish of the Black Sea. Key to marine, brackish-water, euryhaline, and anadromous species with color illustrations, collected by S. V. Bogorodsky. VNIRO Publishing, Moscow, 237 pp. [in Russian, with English abstract]" type="book" year="2007">Vasil’eva 2007</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F00FF97FDEEFF59FCA8FF18" author="Boltachev, A. R. &amp; Karpova, E. P." box="[527,840,223,249]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" refId="ref52296" refString="Boltachev, A. R. &amp; Karpova, E. P. (2017) Marine fishes of the Crimean Peninsula, second edition. Business-Inform, Simpheropol, 376 pp." type="book" year="2017">Boltachev &amp; Karpova 2017</bibRefCitation>
), and requires additional study.
</paragraph>
